Actors represent external entities that interact with the Smart Queue Management System for Banks. Identifying actors helps in understanding system interactions and defining use cases.
The following actors have been identified:
•	Bank Customer
Initiates token generation, views queue status, and receives notifications.
•	Bank Teller /Service Staff
Calls the next customer, serves customers, and manages service counters.
•	Bank Manager/Administrator
Manages system users, service counters, monitors queue performance, and generates reports.
•	Notification System
Sends alerts and notifications to customers when their turn is approaching.
These actors interact with the system to ensure smooth and efficient queue management within bank branches.
